 The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Wednesday night announced that the country has recorded 543 new cases of Coronavirus . The centre, through its twitter handle, further revealed that there are so far 38,344 confirmed cases in Nigeria, with  15,815 patients discharged with 813 deaths recorded The state-by-state breakdown of cases recorded on Wednesday reads thus: Lagos-180 FCT-86 Kaduna-56 Edo-47 Ondo-37 Kwara-35 Ogun-19 Rivers-19 Kano-17 Ebonyi-16 Enugu-16 Delta-7 Bayelsa-4 Bauchi-3 Abia-1  543 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Lagos-180FCT-86Kaduna-56Edo-47Ondo-37Kwara-35Ogun-19Rivers-19Kano-17Ebonyi-16Enugu-16Delta-7Bayelsa-4Bauchi-3Abia-1 38,344 confirmed15,815 discharged813 deaths pic.twitter.com/8J6bMJy6jN — NCDC (@NCDCgov) July 22, 2020 